# Cloudflare static-asset _redirects.
#
# Status code semantics in this file:
#   200 = rewrite (URL bar stays, file at target is served)
#   301/302/307/308 = HTTP redirect (URL bar changes)
#
# We're under `html_handling: "none"` (see wrangler.jsonc), so the
# auto-index-resolution that other Cloudflare modes provide is off
# — every served URL must map either to a literal file path or to
# an explicit rule below.

# Marketing root → serve index.html. Needed because html_handling:
# "none" disables Cloudflare's implicit "/  → /index.html" routing.
/  /index.html  200

# Article share fallback. Every /article/<anything> tap from a
# non-installed device serves the same `article-fallback.html` —
# the page reads the id from `window.location.pathname` and renders
# preview + store redirect. Installed devices NEVER reach this rule
# because iOS Universal Links / Android App Links intercept the URL
# before the browser fetches it.
#
# Target is OUTSIDE /article/ so Wrangler's link validator doesn't
# detect a loop.
/article/*  /article-fallback.html  200

